Masters (MS) in Business Analytics in the USA - Scope, Course Details, Universities

  • 168 Reads
  • 3 min Read
  • By:CANAM Group
  • Updated On:Jun 20,2023 12:08 PM IST

Studying Business Analytics in the USA helps students to acquire experience working with major industries, gain knowledge and meet the demand of the Business analytics sector. This article covers everything applicants need about MS in Business Analytics- Scope, course details and universities.

As the business world overgrows and depends on data, there is a greater demand for employees with a strong analytical and problem-solving skill. A Master’s (MS) in Business Analytics is a graduate program focusing on statistical analysis, data mining and problem-solving strategies for complex business problems.

In today’s competitive era, an understanding of analytics tools and academics is essential to ensure a high level of performance for any business. MS in business analytics is a top-rising STEM program in the USA, with students accessing many academic possibilities and career opportunities. This comprehensive guide explores the top universities, admission requirements, career opportunities and scholarships for Master’s (MS) in Business Analytics in the USA.

Benefits of Pursuing MS in Business Analytics in the USA:

Studying an MS in Business Analytics in the USA can offer several advantages, especially given the importance of data in today's global business environment. Here are some key benefits:

  • High Demand:The demand for data specialists and analysts is increasing in US. Companies require qualified staff to support them in making data-driven decisions.
  • Several Jobs Options:A Business Analytics degree can lead to a variety of professional possibilities. Students can work in several industries, such as Data Analyst, Business Analyst, and Data Scientist.
  • Competitive Salary: Business analytics jobs are often well-paying. Salaries may depend on the role and responsibilities of the individual.
  • Strong Faculty:Universities in the USA often have well-known experts in their field and offer excellent research possibilities.
  • International Acceptance:A degree from a US institute is recognized and valued worldwide. It can provide an advantage in the global operating market.
  • Understanding culture:Students in the USA can learn about the American culture, improve their English skills and live in a multicultural atmosphere.
  • Practical Experience: Most universities in the USA provide internship and co-op programs that allow students to obtain experience while attending classes.

MS in Business Analytics in the USA – Eligibility Criteria

Students must complete the general eligibility requirements to register in top-tier universities. The following are the most general requirements:

  • Transcripts of Academic Records:
    Students must have a bachelor’s or undergraduate degree. Some universities in the USA also require the applicant to submit an academic transcript.
  • GPA or Percentage:
    Individuals must have a 3.0 GPA or higher to be eligible for the business analytics program. It varies from program to program students wish to choose.
  • English Language Proficiency Scores:
    Applicants must submit their English Tests such as IELTS, TOEFL or PTE. The minimum score varies depending on the university students enrol.
  • GMAT or GRE score:
    Universities in the USA accept GRE or GMAT scores, particularly for Master's programs. This test analyses students thinking skills.
  • Experience:
    Some universities in the USA prefer applicants with professional experience in the related field. Internships also get into consideration in the United States (USA).

Documents Required for Business Analytics:

Several documents need to be submitted while applying for MS in Business Analytics. Here are some documents:

  • Educational transcripts
  • Letter of Recommendation (LOR)
  • English Test score (TOEFL, IELTS or PTE)
  • CV or Resume
  • Statement of Purpose (SOP)
  • Passport
  • Passport-size photo
  • Professional experience (if required)
  • Visa proof
  • GRE or GMAT score

MS in Business Analytics in the USA - Application Process:

The application procedure involves some steps which need to be followed. To get started, here’s the overview:

  •  Explore the universities that offer Master in Business Analytics programs
  •  Check the college’s official website for international entry requirements
  •  Pay application fee and apply for the desired university/ college
  •  Make sure all the documents are submitted successfully to avoid delays such as academic transcript, English test scores, etc
  •  Attend the interview (if required)
  •  Once the application is submitted, arrange funds and apply for the visa
  •  Always check the application deadline for the program in the particular intake before applying

Job Opportunities after MS in Business Analytics in the USA:

The market place demand for specialists who understand analytics is growing daily. Jobs for MS in Business Analytics in the USA can be explored across various industries. Here are some of the job titles:

JobsResponsibilities

•    Implementing procedures for data handling.
Data Scientist•    Analyze data.
•    Solve complex business problems.
Analytics Consultant•    Help to make business strategies.
•    Provide expert advice to clients.
Business Analyst •    Identify business problems.
 •    Better understanding of customers’ business strategy.
Senior Business Analyst•    Manage resources, timeline and more.
•    Train or mentor junior business analysts.

What is difference between (a Master of Business Administration) MBA in Business Analytics and a Master’s in Business Analytics in the USA?

Most students want to study Master’s in Data Analytics, while some choose Business Analytics. Check which one is a better option.

Master in Business AnalyticsMBA in Business Analytics
Focus on business analytics.Focus on the world of business.
Develop skills to convert complex data into valuable informationDevelop skills in marketing, finance etc.
Work experience is not mandatory.Work experience is mandatory.
STEM programNot a STEM program
Students study programming and AI subjects.Study finance, accounting and more

Conclusion
Study in the USA is an increasing possibility for Business Analysts worldwide, a Master’s (MS) in Business Analytics is an excellent choice for students to secure a bright future. FAQ

Is MS Data Analytics better than Business Analytics in the USA?
Data analytics works closely with data and Business Analytics is related to business strategies. It depends on the students which field they want to choose.
How long should completing an MS in Business Analytics in the USA take?
The program duration is between 8-24 months, depending on the universities in the USA.
Is the GMAT score mandatory for MS in Business Analytics in the USA?
GMAT or GRE is optional for the MS Business Analytics in the USA.
Is the MS in Business Analytics a STEM-related program in the USA?
Yes, the program is a STEM course, as Business analytics requires an extensive math and technical knowledge understanding.
Who are eligible to apply for MS in Business Analytics in the USA?
Students who completed their bachelor’s degree are eligible for MS Business Analytics in the USA.
